value.name: 12 (number) - Wikipedia
value.snippet: 12 is the fifth Pell number, preceded by 0, 1, 2, and 5, as well as the third pentagonal number. 12 is the superfactorial of 3. It is also a Harshad number in all bases except octal. There are 12 Latin squares of size 3 × 3, where symbols appear exactly once in each row and exactly once in each column.
